<br>  

### When to use Virtual Products

You would use a Virtual Product if you were selling something that wasn't physical like a listing a Decorating Class.

#### Examples

- Birthday parties
- Decorating classes
- Sip & Decorate parties
- Business team building
- Holiday-themed classes
- Church and school functions

### Add a Virtual Product

1. Go to the **Shop Manager > Products** and click **Add Product**.
![Add Product](https://ddxp4ty7t79c7.cloudfront.net/Help%20Scout%20Screenshots/Shop%20Manager/Products/SM%20-%20Products%20-%20Listings%20click%20Add%20Product.png =600x)
2. Fill out the product information for your item. The required info to make your product active: Featured Image, Title, Category, Regular Price.  We recommend you fill out as much of the product information as possible.
   
3. Select the **Simple Product** option under **Product Type**.
![Product Type - Simple Product](https://ddxp4ty7t79c7.cloudfront.net/Help%20Scout%20Screenshots/Shop%20Manager/Products/SM%20-%20Products%20-%20Add%20Product%20-%20Product%20Type.png =600x)
4. Check the box to the left that says **Virtual**.
![Select Virtual](https://ddxp4ty7t79c7.cloudfront.net/Help%20Scout%20Screenshots/Shop%20Manager/Products/SM%20-%20Products%20-%20Add%20Product%20-%20Product%20Type%20-%20Virtual.png =600x)
5. Once you have the product information filled out, click **Save Changes** at the bottom of the page. 

### Edit an existing Virtual Product

1. Go to the **Shop Manager > Products**.
2. Find the product you want to edit.
3. Click **Edit** on the product listing.
4. When you are done with your changes, click **Save Changes** at the bottom of the page. 

